  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6769.91 sitting right between massive negative gamma at 6770 (-14.3B) and 6765 (-12.3B), dealers are in heavy buy mode as they hedge short gamma positions, creating strong support but also amplifying any downside moves. The PIN regime confirms dealers are long gamma overall and will sell rallies toward the 6780 resistance wall (+10.8B) and aggressively buy dips below current levels. The 571% 1-min GEX surge indicates rapid position adjustments, with the 6875 flip strike acting as the key transition level - below it, expect continued dealer buying support with mean reversion bias.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect strong support here with dealers buying dips, but any break below 6765 could accelerate lower.",
